[src:greenplum/postgresql] The query tool includes a scripting language called pgScript for supporting admin and development tasks.
[src:greenplum/postgresql] announced that with the shift towards web-based models, work has begun on pgAdmin 4 with the aim to facilitate cloud deployments.
[src:greenplum/postgresql] PostgreSQL Studio allows users to perform essential PostgreSQL database development tasks from a web-based console.
[src:greenplum/postgresql] PostgreSQL Studio allows users to work with cloud databases without the need to open firewalls.
[src:greenplum/postgresql] AJAX/JavaScript-driven web interface for PostgreSQL.
[src:greenplum/postgresql] Allows browsing, maintaining and creating data and database objects via a web browser.
[src:greenplum/postgresql] management for commonly used scripts, among other features.
[src:greenplum/postgresql] Installers are available for Windows, Macintosh, and Linux, and a simple cross-platform archive that runs from a script.
[src:greenplum/postgresql] Base can be used as a front-end for PostgreSQL.
[src:greenplum/postgresql] The pgBadger PostgreSQL log analyzer generates detailed reports from a PostgreSQL log file.
[src:greenplum/postgresql] pgDevOps is a suite of web tools to install & manage multiple PostgreSQL versions, extensions, and community components, develop SQL queries, monitor running databases and find performance problems.
[src:greenplum/postgresql] is a simple web-based administration tool for PostgreSQL and others, written in PHP.
[src:greenplum/postgresql] pgBackRest is a backup and restore tool for PostgreSQL that provides support for full, differential, and incremental backups.
[src:greenplum/postgresql] pgaudit is a PostgreSQL extension that provides detailed session and/or object audit logging via the standard logging facility provided by PostgreSQL.
[src:greenplum/postgresql] Postgresus is an open source backup tool with GUI for scheduled backups with support of external sources (S3, NAS, FTP, Google Drive, Google Cloud, etc.) and notifications to external services (Slack, Discord, Telegram, SMTP, etc.).
[src:greenplum/postgresql] A number of companies offer proprietary tools for PostgreSQL.
[src:greenplum/postgresql] They often consist of a universal core that is adapted for various specific database products.
[src:greenplum/postgresql] These tools mostly share the administration features with the open source tools but offer improvements in data modeling, importing, exporting or reporting.
[src:greenplum/postgresql] Due to its permissive open-source license and extensible architecture, a broad ecosystem has developed around PostgreSQL.
[src:greenplum/postgresql] This includes numerous companies offering dedicated support and hosting, as well as several forks and derivative databases that adapt PostgreSQL for specific workloads.
